"VT P01DB","Phoenix Dice Box","<b>Dice Boxes</b><BR>If you would much rather roll the dice yourselves, we have here a foam-lined box that allows you to control and contain your dice. The box is a little over 1"" deep and big enough to hold a sheet of paper folded in half. It will even hold a handful of standard-sized miniatures, and then the lid slides right on to hold everything in place. Perfect if you're traveling to the game, or just for game nights at home.<BR><BR><b>Tricking Out The Lid</b><BR>Every dice box has a special locking handle. This small handle lifts slightly to let you slide the box open, and when you're cleaning up, you can drop the handle down and keep the box from accidentally sliding open. Your dice, pencils, miniatures and whatever else will stay in the box, even if the box gets tipped sideways.<BR><BR><div align=""center""><img src=""http://www.boardgamelifestyle.com/images/phoenixbox.jpg"" width=""250"" vspace=5><BR><img src=""http://www.boardgamelifestyle.com/images/phoenixbox1.jpg"" width=""250"" vspace=5></div>","phoenixbox.jpg","",34.60,1,0.80,1999-11-30 00:00:00,2009-02-07 00:00:00,"VixenTor",Active,0,0,2009,N,0.00,N,0,0,0,"Accessories",,,,,,,
